<seg id=1> China Is Speeding Up Establishment Of Human Resource Market System </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Beijing, September 1 (Xinhua News Agency) The Organization Department and Personnel Department of the Party Central Committee recently issued an order to better the planning of Human Resource Market (HRM) and to quicken the HRM development in a healthy manner. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> as is pointed out in the notice, the general goal of the task is that both the employers and employees have the right of free choice while the HRM plays an essential role in the allocation of talents by adjusting supply and demand under the macro control of the nation. There should be better service </seg>
<seg id=4> The immediate goal of the task is: to draw up basic policies and regulations needed by HRMs in 2-3 years, to make HRMs easily available in major cities, to set up regional information-network for HR, to set up HRMs for specialized personnel and regional talents. </seg>
<seg id=5> By 2000, there should be a system of HRMs which provides considerate services and has perfect functioning system and mechanism, timely instructions and legal regulations. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> The Organization Department and Personnel Department of the Party Central Committee demand that organization and personnel administrations of different levels should strengthen the establishment and management of the HRM, better the study and planning in this field, make clear the master plan and implementation steps, and set up a perfect HRM system that is fit to local environment. </seg>
</p>
